= Mac OS X Installer Packages =

Please use the `haskell-platform`. See [https://www.haskell.org/platform/mac.html] for further details. 

Alternatively, a self-contained relocatable binary release for Mac OS X, that avoids the need for putting files in `/usr/bin`, etc, can be found at [https://github.com/ghcformacosx/ghc-dot-app].  This is probably the least intrusive way of getting a version of GHC onto a Mac at present (mid-2014) and will allow you to build GHC from source (other than the documentation).  